@parties
go-to: menu

All legal political parties are a part the National Front coalition. While parties other than the KSČ and the KSS exist, they are powerless, with the Communist Party of Czechoslovakia retaining control in all of them. All parties are structured just like the KSČ, with a secretariat, central committee, and Presidium.

{!<tr><td><div class="box" style='background-color:#DC241F'> </div> !} **KSČ** - *Komunistická strana Československa* (Communist Party of Czechoslovakia) - this is us. We stand for Marxism-Leninism. Following the February 1948 coup, we assumed undisputed power within the country and de facto transformed it into a one-party state. Our power was entrenched in the 1960 Constitution.

{!<tr><td><div class="box" style='background-color:#8B0000'> </div> !} **KSS** - *Komunistická strana Slovenska* (Communist Party of Slovakia) - a slovak branch of the KSČ, founded by the merger of an independent party of the same name and the KSČ in 1948. Just like other non-KSČ parties, it has no independence.

Current relations: [+ kss_relation : relationships +]

{!<tr><td><div class="box" style='background-color:#FAC469'> </div> !} **ČSS** - *Československá strana socialistická* (Czechoslovak Socialist Party) - a nationalist socialist party founded in 1897. Formerly called the *Česká strana národně sociální* (Czech National Social Party), it was one of the biggest opponents of the KSČ before undergoing reformation in 1948 to become more aligned with our party.

Current relations: [+ css_relation : relationships +]

{!<tr><td><div class="box" style='background-color:#FFDC00'> </div> !} **ČSL** - *Československá strana lidová* (Czechoslovak People's Party) - a conservative catholic and the only non-socialist party formed after 1945. During February 1948, it was taken over by its radical communist wing. Many remain in the party as to protest against the regime, and frictions exist between the pro-Communist leadership and members.

Current relations: [+ csl_relation : relationships +]

{!<tr><td><div class="box" style='background-color:#0000FF'> </div> !} **SSO** - *Strana slovenskej obrody* (Party of Slovak Revival) - a political party founded in March 1948 by members of the defunct *Demokratická strana* (Democratic Party) who were willing to cooperate with the KSČ. It is rather conservative.

Current relations: [+ sso_relation : relationships +]

{!<tr><td><div class="box" style='background-color:#1A809A'> </div> !} **SSl** - *Strana slobody* (Freedom Party) - a republican, Christian democratic party founded in 1946 after a split from the *Demokratická strana* (Democratic Party).

Current relations: [+ ssl_relation : relationships +]

{!<tr><td><div class="box" style='background-color:#DCDCDC'> </div> !} **Independents** - various candidates not affiliated with either party. They are generally aligned with the KSČ.

