go-to: neorevisionists if neorevisionism > 0; menu if neorevisionism <= 0

**Internal factions of the KSČ**

Overall dissent: [+ dissent_percent : dissent +]

**Reformists**

The reformist wing of KSČ is relatively new. It emerged at the start of the 60s amidst economic stagnation and increasing criticism leveled at the existing command economy and calls for economic and political reform. It mostly consists of the younger members of the party, some of whom replaced older hardliners.

Strength: [+ reformist_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ reformist_dissent : dissent +]

**Pragmatists**

Pragmatists are the most moderate wing of the party. They support mild reforms, though they are more cautious than other factions. They value stability above everything.

Strength: [+ pragmatist_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ pragmatist_dissent : dissent +]

**Hardliners**

A considerable number of KSČ members are hardliners, opposed to any reform (political or economical) and fully loyal to the ideology of socialism. They believe the KSČ should retain monopoly over Czechoslovak politics and be obedient to Moscow's leadership.

Strength: [+ hardliner_strength : strength +]


